In this statement, the White House Press Secretary informs that the President was briefed on the ongoing efforts to contain the BP oil spill. The President was updated on skimming, dispersing, and burn operations, as well as BP's plans to cut the riser pipe for the placement of an alternate containment device. It is mentioned that the flow rate could increase by 20% until the containment device is applied. The National Incident Commander, Admiral Thad Allen, indicated that government and contractor resources in affected areas will be tripled, as per the President's direction. Efforts to be more responsive to the needs of local communities have also been increased.